attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, for GNU/Linux 2.6.24, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered hacktool. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a statically-linked port scanner. The function `sub_8048e24` implements the core scanning logic, taking an IP block and port as command-line arguments (`Usage: %s <b-block> <port> [c-block]`). It then iterates through IP addresses, creating sockets and attempting to connect, indicative of network reconnaissance. While it contains many legitimate glibc components due to static linking, its primary function is a network utility commonly used in the initial stages of a cyberattack.
